# 7. この気持ちを握りしめて

Taiga: Thanks for the ride.
An's Father: *Sigh* You know I'm not your personal driver, right?
Taiga: Hey, quit being so stuck-up. You've got time until you have to open the cafe, right? Don't leave me hanging now.
An's Father: Acting as you please as always...
An's Father: I mean, what you did was pretty mean.
Taiga: Hah. Like you have any right to talk.
Taiga: So, how's An been?
An's Father: ...
An's Father: She's accepted what Nagi wanted, and she's decided to move forward.
Taiga: Okay...
Taiga: So, does that mean you've put all this behind you now?
An's Father: No, not yet.
Taiga: Hm?
An's Father: There's still something I need to do.
Taiga: I see. I guess Nagi's still got a hold over you.
An's Father: Not her. I'm talking about my duty to An and the next generation.
Taiga: They're probably at school now, right...?
Taiga: Being a student's so tough. You never have enough time to really sing.
An's Father: You're joking, right? Only people who actually studied get to say stuff like that.
Taiga: Haha. True.
An's Father: Anyway, I need to head back.
Taiga: Alright. Later, Ken.
Taiga: Oh, also... Your coffee wasn't half bad.
An's Father: Thanks.
Taiga: I still have time, but I guess I should start making my way over now that I'm checked in...
Taiga: The folks at that record company are probably gonna chew me out when I get back.
Taiga: (I guess I have that girl to blame...)
Taiga: Hm? That looks like...
Taiga: What's she doing here...?
Kohane: Oh...! Taiga!
Taiga: You're all here...
Taiga: It's the middle of the day. Shouldn't you be in school...?
Kohane: U-Um, so...
Kohane: W-We're cutting class!
Taiga: Whoa, hold on... Someone's been a bad influence on you.
An: Uncle Taiga...
An: You'll be boarding your flight soon, right? We want to tell you something before you do.
An: I heard everything about Aunt Nagi. About her, about Dad, about you. All of it.
Taiga: I see...
Taiga: Looks like you've all made up your minds.
An: We have. We're gonna answer her call...
An: But that doesn't mean I'm forgiving you...!
An: Of course, I know telling you to apologize would be pointless, especially since you never apologize to anyone...
An: So... We're gonna see what's beyond you guys' dream! That's what'll get under your skin the most, right?
Toya: We're serious about this. And we don't care how long it takes us...
Akito: So, just wait for us over there.
Taiga: Alright... I'll be looking forward to seeing you all again.
Kohane: Taiga.
Kohane: There's something I need to tell you.
Taiga: Hm? What's up?
Kohane: Thank you for everything you've done!
Kohane: You taught me so much about so many different things...
Kohane: Like what it means to sing... Taking us to COL because I didn't actually see RAD WEEKEND when it happened...
Kohane: And our third event went as well as it did because of what you taught me.
Kohane: And you showed me...
Kohane: This frustration that I feel.
Kohane: I... I'm going to move forward without forgetting this frustration.
Kohane: I don't care how long or scary the road up ahead is! I'm not stopping!
Kohane: We're going to find an even greater purpose for singing than you, perform even better than you...
Kohane: We're going to surpass RAD WEEKEND and see what's waiting for us on the other side!
Taiga: Knock yourselves out...
Kohane: We will!
